18 B. The policy adopted by a school district board of education
19 for the investigation of reported incidents of bullying or
20 threatening behavior pursuant to this section shall include:
21 1. A statement, relating to victims of bullying, that the
22 school district prohibits, does not have, and will not adopt, in
23 name or in practice, a zero-tolerance disciplinary policy. For the
24 purposes of this section, “zero-tolerance disciplinary policy” means
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB792 SFLR Page 6
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 a po licy or practice of discipline that results in an automatic
2 disciplinary consequence such as suspension or expulsion for any
3 student who commits one or more acts of school violence or violent
4 behavior even if school district administrators have some discretion
5 to modify the consequence on a case-by-case basis; and
6 2. A statement relating to students who engage in self-defense,
7 pursuant to paragraph 9 of subsection A of this section, that the
8 school district administration, when determining the disciplinary
9 action for the student who has committed an act of school violence
10 or exhibited violent behavior, will take into account if such act
11 was committed in self-defense as an immediate response to an act of
12 school violence or violent behavior committed by another student.
13 C. In developing the policy, the school district board of
14 education shall make an effort to involve the teachers, parents,
15 administrators, school staff, school volunteers, community
16 representatives, local law enforcement agencies, and students. The
17 students, teachers, and parents or guardian of every child residing
18 within a school district shall be notified by the school district
19 board of education of its adoption of the policy and shall receive a
20 copy upon request. The school district policy shall be implemented
21 in a manner that is ongoing throughout the school year and is
22 integrated with other violence prevention efforts.
23 C. D. The teacher of a child attending a public school shall
24 have the same right as a parent or guardian to control and
